The paper discusses an algorithm for modeling and controlling crowdsourced work, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a particle filter to reduce computation time and memory usage suggests a focus on computational efficiency (cs.CE) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the experiments conducted to compare the performance of the algorithm fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
